==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
Pinyin: Jiāozhǐ (jiao1 zhi3)
===Cantonese===
**Jyutping:

===Etymology===
*From [[交]] ("mix," "intersect," "exchange," "communicate," "deliver") + [[趾]] ("toe," "tracks," "footprints")
*In the time of [[wikipedia:Yao (ruler)|Tang Yao]], the term Jiaozhi referred to anything south of the Five Ridges (Dayu, Qitian, Dupang, Mengzhu and Yuecheng) of Guangdong and Guangxi.  During the [[wikipedia:Han Dynasty|Han Dynasty]], Jiaozhi was established as the Jiaozhi Commandery ('''交趾'''[[郡]]) for the administrative control of what is now the northern part of [[Vietnam]].

===Proper noun===
'''[[交]][[趾]]''' (traditional and simplified)

# an ancient name for the northern part of [[Vietnam]]

